<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	App Sandbox is intentionally disabled because OpenBurnBar requires filesystem access to read
	AI agent log files from various locations in the user's home directory:
	- ~/.claude/projects/ (Claude Code sessions)
	- ~/.factory/sessions/ (Factory/Droid sessions)
	- ~/.codex/ (Codex sessions)
	- ~/.kimi/sessions/ (Kimi sessions)
	- And other agent-specific directories

	Enabling sandbox would require either:
	1. User to grant access to each directory individually via security-scoped bookmarks
	2. Limiting support to only bundled/default log locations

	The app is distributed via Developer ID signing (not App Store) which provides
	an alternative security boundary through Gatekeeper and notarization.

	See: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/security/app-sandbox
	-->
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<false/>
	<key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-only</key>
	<true/>
	<!-- Firebase Auth (and other Firebase SDKs) use kSecUseDataProtectionKeychain on macOS; Keychain Sharing is required so the app can use that access group. https://firebase.google.com/docs/ios/troubleshooting-faq -->
	<key>keychain-access-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)com.openburnbar.app</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-container-identifiers</key>
	<array>
		<string>iCloud.com.openburnbar.app</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-services</key>
	<array>
		<string>CloudDocuments</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
